    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-17T18:51:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-17T18:51:00-05:00" n="542"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d542">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/5–1754: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d542fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_RGH1"
                            >Raynor</persName> of <gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_BNA1">BNA</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-17T19:51:00-04:00"
                            >May 17, 1954—7:51 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 190. Limit distribution. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName> today separately saw New Zealand,
                    Australian and British Ambassadors at their request. Informed them he thought
                    general agreement just about reached on holding five-power military staff talks
                    which we desire held Washington without fanfare. Also indicated we intend
                    continue parallel talks with broader group interested states, bilaterally if
                    necessary, on question development regional security arrangements.</p>
                <p>Also reviewed with each of them in general terms talks which have taken place
                    with French.</p>
                <p>Ambassadors in the main listened although <persName corresp="#p_MLK1"
                        >Munro</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_SSPC1">Spender</persName> by
                    referring to <persName corresp="#p_WTC1">Webb</persName>’s and <persName
                        corresp="#p_CRG1">Casey</persName>’s statements gave impression they feel
                    political talks should go forward as matter of urgency. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MLK1">Munro</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MSRM1"
                        >Makins</persName> both also queried what French were doing on matter
                    independence. <persName corresp="#p_MLK1">Munro</persName> inquired if we had
                    received any approach similar to French from Associated States. He also probed
                    into question of what type of <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> action US had in
                    mind.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MSRM1">Makins</persName> indicated <persName
                        corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> keeping India, Pakistan and Ceylon informed
                    closely re Geneva developments. He expressed the view that all three might come
                    in with respect to a settlement provided settlement were guaranteed
                    multilaterally by both sides. <persName corresp="#p_MSRM1">Makins</persName>
                    added that in so far as he knew there had been no discussion or suggestion that
                        <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> had in mind that these States
                    would come into a collective security arrangement as members.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d542fn2">Memoranda of conversation, May 17, are filed in
                        751G.00/5–1754.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
